In much the same way that Jira Service Desk is a fantastic support tool for communities, questions can also be a fantastic knowledge base!

For 'open' communities such as API/outreach programs and 'freemium' versions of products, questions is a cost prohibitive solution due to the pricing-per-participant model.  

Confluence questions is IMHO the best non-SO and on-premise solution in the market today.  It would be fantastic to see a pricing model that embraces communities with a large volume of participants by charging instead for the number of moderators (in a similar way that Service Desk prices per agent).  [@JIRAServiceDesk agrees|https://twitter.com/JIRAServiceDesk/status/702241544439463937]

